# Research

This folder contains peer-reviewed and institutional research
referenced in the CV and portfolio of Bilgin Can Isikoglu.

## Purpose

These papers provide independent academic evidence supporting
skill-based hiring as a functional equivalent to formal degree
credentials in AI-related professions.

## Papers

### Skill-Based Hiring for AI Roles

**Gonzalez Ehlinger & Stephany (2023)**
Skills or Degree? The Rise of Skill-Based Hiring for AI and Green Jobs
- Source: arXiv / Oxford Internet Institute
- arXiv: https://arxiv.org/abs/2312.11942
- File: skill-based-hiring-AI-Stephany-2023.pdf

**Gonzalez Ehlinger & Stephany (2025)**
Skills or degree? The rise of skill-based hiring for AI and green jobs
- Source: ScienceDirect / Technological Forecasting and Social Change
- DOI: https://www.sciencedirect.com/article/pii/S0040162525000733
- File: skill-based-hiring-AI-ScienceDirect-2025.pdf

## Key Finding

Employers have initiated skill-based hiring for AI roles,
adopting flexible hiring practices that prioritize demonstrated
competency over formal qualifications.
Portfolio evidence constitutes functional equivalent to
academic credentials in this professional category.
